{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
'''Adventure Parks Group''' was a company that used to run and operate two theme parks in the [[U.S. state]]s of [[Florida]] and [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]]. They are [[Wild Adventures]] in [[Valdosta, GA|Valdosta, Georgia]] and [[Cypress Gardens|Cypress Gardens Adventure Park]] in [[Winter Haven, Florida]]. It also owned a radio station in South Georgia called Wild Adventures Radio 92.1FM. Due to Bankruptcy problems, both parks have been sold off. Wild Adventures was sold to the [[Herschend Family Entertainment Corporation]] and Cypress Gardens was sold to Land South Holdings.

