{{Infobox company | name = CrowdRise | trading_name = | logo = [[File:CrowdriseLogo.gif|200px|CrowdRise]] | caption = | type = [[Private company|Private]] | traded_as = | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = {{start date and age|2010|5|19}}<ref name="PaisPeretti2014">{{cite book |author1=Ivana Pais |author2=Paola Peretti |author3=Chiara Spinelli |title=Crowdfunding: La via collaborativa all'imprenditorialità |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gJnbCgAAQBAJ&pg=PT36 |date=2014-09-09 |publisher=EGEA spa |isbn=978-88-238-7669-9 |pages=36–}}</ref> | founder = | defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | location_city = [[Detroit]], [[Michigan]] | location_country = [[United States|U.S.]] | locations = | area_served = | key_people = [[Edward Norton]], [[Shauna Robertson]], Robert Wolfe, {{cite web|title=Jeffrey Wolfe|url=https://angel.co/jeffreywolfe}} | industry = [[Online fundraising]] | products = | production = | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | aum = <!-- Only used with financial services companies --> | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = {{URL|http://crowdrise.com}} | footnotes =<ref name=Wallace2010>{{cite news |last=Wallace |first=Amy |title=Online Giving Meets Social Networking |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/09/05/business/05proto.html |accessdate=29 November 2012 |newspaper=The New York Times |date=5 September 2010}}</ref> }}
'''CrowdRise''' is a for-profit [[crowdfunding]] platform that raises charitable donations.<ref name=Wallace2010 /><ref name="ThompsonKhambaita2016">{{cite book |author1=Matrix Thompson |author2=Sarika Khambaita |title=Who Is Winning The Social Media and Crowd Funding War: The Battle For Good Vs Evil - Will You Be A Casualty Or Emerge As A Trailblazer? |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JDBzCwAAQBAJ&pg=PT43 |date=25 January 2016 |publisher=Pamper Me Network |pages=43– |quote=... CrowdRise is the world's largest and fastest growing fundraising platform dedicated exclusively to charitable giving. ...}}</ref> CrowdRise was founded by [[Edward Norton]], [[Shauna Robertson]], and the founders of [[Moosejaw]], Robert and Jeffrey Wolfe.<ref name=Wallace2010 /><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2010/05/13/crowdrise-ed-norton-launc_n_575124.html |title=CrowdRise: Ed Norton Launches Fundraising And Volunteerism Site |publisher=Huffington Post |date=2011-05-26 |accessdate=November 30, 2012}}</ref><ref name="Harvey2013">{{cite book |author=Kerric Harvey |title=Encyclopedia of Social Media and Politics |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qS91AwAAQBAJ&pg=PA14 |date=20 December 2013 |publisher=SAGE Publications |isbn=978-1-4522-9026-3 |pages=14– |quote=Edward Norton cofounded Crowdrise, which is ... Crowdrise allows users to tap into their social networks to raise funds for their charitable causes. Celebrities such as ... Crowdrise allows users to create a microsite to raise money for a cause.}}</ref><ref name="Leeke2013">{{cite book |author=Ananda Kiamsha Madelyn Leeke |title=Digital Sisterhood: A Memoir of Fierce Living Online |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hdj8AAAAQBAJ&pg=PA277 |date=September 2013 |publisher=iUniverse |isbn=978-1-4917-0639-8 |pages=277– |quote=Nonprofit Organizations and Social Causes Women • Crowdrise.com is an online fundraising web site that allows individual fundraisers, nonprofit fundraising, and event fundraising (co-founded by female film producer Shauna Robertson).}}</ref> CrowdRise was acquired in 2017 by [[GoFundMe]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/susanadams/2017/01/10/gofundme-crosses-into-unicorn-territory-with-crowdrise-acquisition/#1d0926637fa0|title=GoFundMe Buys Rival CrowdRise |author=Susan Adams|date=10 January 2017|publisher=Forbes}}</ref>
== Overview == CrowdRise's fundraising model is based upon the notion of making giving back fun,<ref name="Wallace2015">{{cite book |author=Patricia Wallace |title=The Psychology of the Internet |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IIOpCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA161 |date=26 November 2015 |publisher=Cambridge University Press |isbn=978-1-107-07913-7 |pages=161– |quote=Actor Edward Norton promotes the site called Crowdrise.com, which takes an offbeat and often humorous approach to crowdfunding for good causes. It adds contests, social networking, and a community feel designed to appeal to younger ...}}</ref> which may lead to more people donating and more funds being raised.<ref name="Lopez2014">{{cite book |author=Shane J. Lopez |title=Making Hope Happen: Create the Future You Want for Yourself and Others |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ThcHBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA171 |date=22 July 2014 |publisher=Simon and Schuster |isbn=978-1-4516-6623-6 |pages=171– |quote=Crowdrise.com, founded by Robert Wolfe and a cast of characters including actor Ed Norton, has a different focus. It helps individuals and groups raise funds to bankroll a community project or charity. Once you sign up on the website, you can ...}}</ref> The platform uses gamification and a rewards point system to engage users to participate in fundraising and donating.<ref name="Petruzzi2015">{{cite book |author=Vincenzo Petruzzi |title=Il potere della Gamification. Usare il gioco per creare cambiamenti nei comportamenti e nelle performance individuali: Usare il gioco per creare cambiamenti nei comportamenti e nelle performance individuali |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Ve6JCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA97 |date=4 June 2015 |publisher=FrancoAngeli |language=Italian |isbn=978-88-917-1294-3 |pages=97–}}</ref>
Its primary model is donation-based, and the campaign defaults to keep-what-you-raise.
Their default "Starter" pricing is to charge the non-profit a 5% platform fee from each donation, plus a payment processing fee (credit card fee) of 2.9% + $0.30 per donation.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fundraising.crowdrise.com/nonprofit-pricing|title=Non-profit pricing|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Crowdrise.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|accessdate=July 18, 2018|quote="Free to get started. 5% platform fee. 2.9% + 0.30 payment processing."}}</ref> Donors may choose whether to pay the fee in addition to the amount of their donation or to have the fee subtracted from their donation amount before being delivered.<ref name="fees">{{cite web|title=What are these fees for? Do I have to pay them?|url=https://support.crowdrise.com/hc/en-us/articles/115013339368-What-are-these-fees-for-Do-I-have-to-pay-them-|website=Crowdrise|accessdate=11 July 2018}}</ref>
