{{Infobox building | name = Fukui Fine Arts Museum | native_name = 福井県立美術館 | image = Celebrating the New Year by Kimura Buzan (Fukui Fine Arts Museum)L.jpg | caption = Celebrating the New Year by [[Kimura Buzan]] | cost = | owner = | address = 3-16-1 Bunkyō | location_town = [[Fukui, Fukui|Fukui]], [[Fukui Prefecture]] | location_country = [[Japan]] | coordinates = {{coord|36.078530|N|136.215234|E|display=title,inline|format=dms|type:landmark_region:JP_scale:10000}} | opened_date = 1 November 1977 | inauguration_date = | renovation_date = | demolition_date = | destruction_date = | other_dimensions = | floor_count = | floor_area = | architect = | architecture_firm = | url = {{homepage|http://info.pref.fukui.jp/bunka/bijutukan/bunka1.html}} }}
{{nihongo|'''Fukui Fine Arts Museum'''|福井県立美術館|Fukui kenritsu bijutsukan}} opened in [[Fukui, Fukui|Fukui]], [[Fukui Prefecture]], Japan, in 1977. The collection, numbering some 2,840 pieces, includes prints by [[Francisco Goya|Goya]] and [[Picasso]] and paintings by [[Iwasa Matabei]] and artists associated with [[Okakura Tenshin]] and the beginnings of the [[Nihon Bijutsuin]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://bunka.nii.ac.jp/museums/detail/302 |script-title=ja:福井県立美術館 |trans-title=Fukui Fine Arts Museum |language=Japanese |publisher=[[Agency for Cultural Affairs]] |accessdate=14 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://info.pref.fukui.jp/bunka/bijutukan/image/top/general_information.pdf |title=General Information |publisher=Fukui Fine Arts Museum |accessdate=14 October 2015}}</ref> The museum played and important role for contemporary artist [[Ay-O]] by hosting his first retrospective in 2006. ==See also== * [[Fukui Prefectural Museum of Cultural History]] * [[List of Cultural Properties of Japan - paintings (Fukui)]]
