{{Infobox album | name = In Spite of Wishing and Wanting | type = Soundtrack | artist = David Byrne | cover = David Byrne - In Spite of Wishing and Wanting.jpg | alt = | released = {{Startdate|1999}} | recorded = | venue = | studio = | genre = | length = | label = Self-released | producer = David Byrne | prev_title = [[Feelings (David Byrne album)|Feelings]] | prev_year = 1997 | next_title = [[Look into the Eyeball]] | next_year = 2001 }} '''''In Spite of Wishing and Wanting''''' is a 1999 soundtrack by [[David Byrne]] for the performance of the same name by the [[Ultima Vez]] dance company. It features original compositions as well as [[remix]]es from Byrne's previous album ''[[Feelings (David Byrne album)|Feelings]]''. Byrne sold the album through his web site and live performances for a limited time.
As indicated in the [[liner notes]], Byrne first saw Ultima Vez in Seattle in 1991 and kept in contact for several years before deciding to write the music for a show based on the fiction of [[Julio Cortázar]].
==Track listing== All tracks composed by David Byrne, except where noted #"Horses"&nbsp;– 4:31 #"Sleeping Up"&nbsp;– 12:13 #"Speech"&nbsp;– 5:26 #"Saïd & the Ants"&nbsp;– 4:18 #"Fear"&nbsp;– 2:32 #"Fuzzy Freaky" ([[DJ Food]] Mix) (Byrne, [[Danielle Fossatti]])&nbsp;– 6:19 #"Danceonvaselinesuperextendedremix"&nbsp;– 19:45
==External links== *[http://www.ultimavez.com/com/ Ultima Vez homepage] *{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r712348}}
