{{Infobox venue |name=Koishikawa Football Stadium |nickname= |native_name=小石川サッカー場 |native_name_lang= |fullname= |former names= |logo_image= |logo_caption= |image=Koishikawa Korakuen (2008.09).JPG |image_size= |image_alt= |caption= |pushpin_map= |pushpin_mapsize= |pushpin_map_caption= |pushpin_label_position= |address= |location={{flagicon|Japan}} [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]] |coordinates= |type= |genre= |broke_ground= |built= |opened= |renovated= |expanded= |closed= |demolished= |owner= |operator= |surface= |scoreboard= |production= |cost= |architect= |builder= |project_manager= |structural engineer= |services engineer= |general_contractor= |main_contractors= |seating_type= |capacity= |suites= |record_attendance= |dimensions= |field_shape= |acreage= |volume= |tenants= |embedded= |website= |publictransit= }} {{nihongo|'''Koishikawa Football Stadium'''|小石川サッカー場}} is a [[Association football|football]] [[stadium]] in [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]].
It hosted the [[1959 Emperor's Cup]] and [[1959 Emperor's Cup Final|final]] game between [[Kwangaku Club]] and [[Chuo University]] was played there on May 6, 1959.
